data.name: AdvancedConfig.AcknowledgeMessageDelay.Description
data.value: Determines the time taken for an unacknowledged event to be acknowledged.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AcquireWakeLock.Description
data.value: Prevent sleep, auto-locking, screen savers, and inactivity disconnection while you're idle.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AgentKeepAliveInterval.Description
data.value: Governs the keep alive signal interval for access client.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AllowGuestInitiatedFileTransfer.Description
data.value: Allow the guest to initiate file transfers to the host machine.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AllowLoginCredentialsStorage.Description
data.value: Shows an item within the tray icon's context menu clicking on which would open a form that would help guests to store their Windows login credentials.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AllowPasswordAutoComplete.Description
data.value: Enables password auto-complete for user logins.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AlwaysDeleteSession.Description
data.value: Automatically delete support sessions on exit.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AlwaysOnTop.Description
data.value: Keep the host and guest client windows on top of other windows.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ApplicationKeepAliveInterval.Description
data.value: Determines how often a client will send application-level keep alives to the server.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AuthenticationRequired.Description
data.value: Determines the minimum number of authentication factors that must be associated with a user in order for the user to log into the Host and/or Administration page.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AuthenticationRequired.Option1
data.value: No required minimum number of authentication factors

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AuthenticationRequired.Option2
data.value: Require at least one authentication factor (e.g., password only)

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AuthenticationRequired.Option3
data.value: Require at least two authentication factors (e.g., password and OTP)

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AutoConsent.Description
data.value: Automatically consent to control if no user process is running on the guest machine.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AutoConsentCountdown.Description
data.value: Enable a countdown before the consent-to-connect prompt disappears and the host is automatically connected to a session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AutoConsentToBackstage.Description
data.value: Enable switching to the backstage logon session without another consent prompt.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.AutoRenewSessionTimeout.Description
data.value: Check this setting to automatically disconnect the host from sessions after the time specified for AccessTokenExpireSeconds

data.name: AdvancedConfig.BeepOnConnect.Description
data.value: Make the host client beep when a guest connects to the session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.BitmaskSettings.Caution
data.value: Caution: Changing bitmask settings can cause undesirable results. Ensure you understand how the host and/or guest clients will change before saving setting values.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.BlankGuestMonitor.Description
data.value: Blanks the guest's monitor(s) and displays a blank screen message.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.BlockGuestInput.Description
data.value: Blocks the guest's input when the host shares their screen.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.BlockIpAddresses.Description
data.value: Block one or more IP addresses in a comma-separated list, or specify a range of IP addresses by using CIDR notation.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ClearAnnotations.Description
data.value: Clears any annotations from the screen.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ClientServiceTimeout.Description
data.value: Sets the delay before the end-of-session dialog disappears.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ColorTheme.Description
data.value: Sets the application color theme for the host client.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.CommandCharacterReturnCount.Description
data.value: Determines the max number of characters returned for commands ran via the Commands tab.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.CommandExecutionTimeout.Description
data.value: Determines how long after execution to kill a command.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ConsentTimeout.Description
data.value: When a partner provides consent to control, that consent will expire after this many seconds.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.CookieSameSiteMode.Description
data.value: Specifies the value of the SameSite attribute for browser cookies set by Control.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DefaultScreenQuality.Description
data.value: Determines the default screen capture quality level.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DefaultSession.Description
data.value: Enables specific host client features by default for all sessions.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DefaultSoundMode.Description
data.value: Sets the default sound mode for all sessions of a session type.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DirectorySettings.Description
data.value: Directory settings change the directory to which files are saved. Directories can be specified using absolute or relative file paths.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DisableClipboardCapture.Description
data.value: Disable clipboard capture in a session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DisconnectParticipant.Description
data.value: Force disconnects a participant from a session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.DuoSettings.Description
data.value: Once configured with a Duo account, ScreenConnect will send a login request to a user's mobile device when that user attempts to log into the instance. Once the user approves the login request on their mobile device, the user can proceed to the ScreenConnect Host page.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.EmptySessionProgramsToStart.Description
data.value: Specifies the programs that are automatically started upon entering the backstage logon session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.EnableClipboardHelpHelper.Description
data.value: Let the helper automatically search using the text in the host's clipboard.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.EnableSSLForEmail.Description
data.value: Specifies whether or not SMTP requests are to use SSL.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ExitConnectionBanner.Description
data.value: Enables the "Exit" option for support sessions in the connection banner's menu.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.FullScreenWhenMaximized.Description
data.value: View guest machines in full screen mode when host client is maximized.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.GuestInformationRefreshInterval.Caution
data.value: Caution: Setting this value lower than 300 seconds may adversely affect performance.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.GuestInformationRefreshInterval.Description
data.value: Controls the number of seconds between refreshes of guest information in the General tab on the Host page.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.GuestScreenPreview.Description
data.value: Controls the quality and size of the guest desktop screenshot displayed on the host page.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HideConnectionBanner.Description
data.value: Enables the "Hide" option in the connection banner's menu.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HideGuestWallpaper.Description
data.value: Hide the user's desktop wallpaper in a session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostAuthenticationDuration.Description
data.value: Determines the length for which authentication tickets are issued/reissued.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostClientDeviceFingerprintValidationLevel
data.value: Host Client Device Fingerprint Validation Level

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostClientDeviceFingerprintValidationLevel.Description
data.value: Specifies if incoming connections should be rejected if the IP address doesn't match the one in the included access token.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostClientDeviceFingerprintValidationLevel.DescriptionHigh
data.value: High: passes if the access token IP address matches the connection IP address

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostClientDeviceFingerprintValidationLevel.DescriptionLow
data.value: Low: like Medium, but will also pass if access token and connection IP addresses are from different address families (ex. IPv4 vs IPv6)

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostClientDeviceFingerprintValidationLevel.DescriptionMedium
data.value: Medium: like High, but will also pass if the IP address from either the access token or the connection is unavailable

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostConnectionTimeout.Description
data.value: Disconnects an idle host from session after a certain number of seconds.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostSessionDisplayLimit.Description
data.value: Specifies the maximum number of sessions to display on the host page.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.HostTransferTimeout.Description
data.value: Specifies how long a host must be logged out of the ScreenConnect web portal before they are ineligible to receive a transferred session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.IsBackstageDefault.Description
data.value: Join into the backstage logon session by default.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.IsUserAllowedToRequireConsent
data.value: Is User Allowed to Require Consent

data.name: AdvancedConfig.IsUserAllowedToRequireConsent.Description
data.value: Enables the "Require Consent" toggle in the guest client UI

data.name: AdvancedConfig.KeepClientOnTop.Description
data.value: Selects whether or not the status window is always on top.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.LockGuestMachine.Description
data.value: Locks guest machine when host disconnects.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.LockMachineOnConnect.Description
data.value: Automatically lock the guest machine when a host connects.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ManageCredentials.Description

data.name: AdvancedConfig.NavigateToolboxFolder.Description
data.value: Navigates to the toolbox folder from the client window.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.OpenConnectionBanner.Description
data.value: Enables the "Open" option in the connection banner's menu.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.OpenSessionTimeout.Description
data.value: Specifies the period before a host will have to relaunch a session (Support, Access, or Meeting). Also determines how long a downloaded launcher file can be used to connect to a session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.PageIdleTimeout.Description
data.value: Idle users will be logged out of the Host and Administration pages after this many seconds.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.PauseVideo.Description
data.value: Pauses the recording of the current session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.Reboot.Description

data.value: Retrieves entire folders from the guest machine via the session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.RecordVideo.Description
data.value: Records video of the current session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.RelayAddressableUri.Description

data.name: AdvancedConfig.RemotePrinting.Description

data.value: Runs a tool from the toolbox on the guest machine.

data.value: Runs a tool from the toolbox on the guest machine with elevated privileges.

data.value: The following error occured while attempting to save changes to app.config:

data.name: AdvancedConfig.SelectAnnotationMode.Description

data.name: AdvancedConfig.SelectLogonSession.Description
data.value: Allows the host to choose which guest logon session to view.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.SelectProviderHelper.Description

data.value: Sends entire folders to the guest machine via the session.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ShowCloseSessionDialog.Description

data.value: Randomly display a small feedback survey for hosts at the end of a session. This survey appears sporadically and will help us improve the product.

data.value: Show the notification balloon when minimizing the guest client.

data.name: AdvancedConfig.ShowSystemTrayIcon.Description
